posts.name: R. Nashburn
posts.cooked: The correct drill size for a 1/4-20 tap is a #7 drill per the Machinists handbook.  The diameter of the #7 drill is 0.201.   That is where the 0.201 diameter comes from.
Just did the math. To save 1 lb. from changing your holes from .2 in to .201 in, you‚Äôd need 130,000 holes on 0.25 inch thick aluminum. (:
